description: Published in September 2005 by Panini, the first of a new series of Doctor Who Annuals to tie in with the revived TV show. Featuring the Chris Eccleston ninth Doctor, as with the prior Doctor Who Annuals and Doctor Who Yearbooks, it included a mixture of features, illustrated text stories and comic strips. Its success led to two volumes being released the next year, another Annual plus the first of the new Doctor Who Storybook series.
name: Doctor Who Annual

description: In search of his kidnapped bride, Andrew Cain is in Darkwood with his Tuareg warriors, ready to give a hand to Zagor against the Kushite negomancers and their living corpses. But an enemy plots in the shadows. Even the archaeologist Dexter Green will soon be, in spite of himself, in the game, but against our heroes is preparing a deadly weapon and invincible: the sinister god of dust that destroys everything on his way.
name: I negromanti di Kush

description: On the way back to Darkwood, returning from the swamps of Waterwall, Zagor and Cico encounter a singular traveler, the explorer Dexter Green, accompanied by his servant, Yambo, and their even more unusual cargo: the mummy of a Sumerian king, who the two intend to supply to the Museum of Richmond. Upon Joining them, them, our friends find themselves in the austere halls of the museum two old acquaintances, Professor Oldbones and the private investigator Bat Batterton.
name: Il segreto dei Sumeri

description:
This exciting foray into the official Marvel Cinematic Universe is just in time for the Avengers blockbuster movie! How will S.H.I.E.L.D. maintain the status quo in a world full of green monsters, gods, and men in iron suits?

---

Part 1 (of 8) of the prelude mini-series reintroducing the characters in the upcoming Avengers movie.
name: Chapter One

volume.name: Marvel's The Avengers Prelude: Fury's Big Week

description: The mummy of the ancient Sumerian king Dumizi, donated by Professor Dexter Green to the Museum of Richmond, is not a simple archaeological find. For the followers of the cult of Namtar, its removal from the temple in which it reposed is a sacrilege to be avenged with blood. Among the various enemies that Zagor , Cico and Bat Batterton will face, there are also an archeologist rival Green, Professor Richter, interested in a tiara with sinister powers and that was part of the funeral, and Velasquez, a Mexican adventurer.
name: Terrore al Museo

description:
95.5% of humanity is dead. All that is left are settlements dotted throughout the landscape. In this kill or be killed environment the peaceful settlement of Kranburn cannot continue to take the passive route when might equals right and a mad dictator to the north has every intention of destroying them.

Kranburn is a story seen mostly from the point of view of Brand, a resident of Kranburn.

In 1992 a plague ravaged the world. Totally unprepared for the fast spreading illness mankind was made nearly extinct, with only .5% being immune and seeing 1993. Fast forward to the year 2015 and life has stuttered but continued, mostly in the form of strongholds and settlements. This story follows the settlement of Kranburn, a small town built on what was once the rooftop car park of an old shopping centre.
name: Chapter 1

description: Final issue! An epic, jaw-dropping finale you can't miss from Coheed and Cambria's Claudio Sanchez (The Amory Wars) and Chondra Echert (Kill Audio)! With the one man holding the key buried in chains, the two remaining human factions in zombie-filled New York City are ready for war. Will Ewing be able to escape his shackles and exact his revenge - or will a triumphant Lavoe finish what he started? All this in the pulse-pounding conclusion that redefines the zombie genre!

It's the poisonous fruit of Loki's trickery during the Siege, as the God of Thunder battles demons and monsters to cross from one side of the desolate dimension to the other! At stake...his life and the fate of all Asgardians!

Also, an incredible new Captain America adventure begins! Where has the Captain America from the '50s been and how has our modern world welcomed him? And what will Steve and Bucky do when an old enemy tries to become a revolutionary?

Plus, the incredible Worlds Most wanted reaches its amazing conclusion! Brace yourselves, Trur Believers for the final showdown between Iron Man and the Iron Patriot!!!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #602, Thor VOL.1 #613 and Invincible Iron Man Vol. 5 #19!
name: Thor In Hell!
Superboy und die Legion Der Superhelden

description:
The three most inevitable things in the world are death, taxes and another Groo miniseries from Dark Horse. This one is about the other two: Groo and his loyal pooch Rufferto encounter a king who is forever raising the cost of living and an undertaker who drives up the cost of dying. The Eisner-winning team of Sergio Aragons and Mark Evanier do it again ... whatever "it" is.

Groo takes a vow not to slay.

Groo has taken a fearsome pledge: no more killing! And if you think that makes him any less dangerous, you don't know Groo. He's even worse ... as the savage warrior, Odoman the Invincible, finds out the hard way. It's the second issue of four from the Eisner-winning team of Sergio Aragones and Mark Evanier, doing what they do best!

Odoman, Gorsh, and Vorpal set out to slay Groo, while the king and undertaker are having trouble making ends meet.

And so the village goes to war against ... well, they're not exactly sure of that part yet. But they're definitely going to war. What a time for Groo to be trapped in his solemn vow not to kill! Of all the parts of this exciting miniseries by the award-winning duo of Sergio Aragons and Mark Evanier, this is probably the third.

The three warriors battle to see who gets to kill Groo.

The fourth and final part of the only miniseries that dares to ask the question: How long can Groo go without killing someone? (We're guessing page three.) The award-winning combo of Sergio Aragons and Mark Evanier are sure hoping they can wrap up this epic tale of war, royalty, barbarians, barbecued ribs, undertakers, and a really, really stupid title character.

Groo becomes a champion while the Eastern Plains go to war.

volume.name: New Kids On The Block: NKOTB

description:
The Complete Little Orphan Annie is the second series to be released under IDW's The Library of American Comics imprint, edited and designed by Dean Mullaney.

Volume One will contain more than 1,000 daily comics in nine complete stories, from the very first strip in August 1924 through October 1927. In the pages of "Will Tomorrow Ever Come?" readers will discover how Annie escapes the orphanage and is ultimately adopted by "Daddy;" how she finds that loveable mutt Sandy and rescues him from being tortured; how she meets the Silos, who become recurring characters throughout the series; how she joins the circus and first encounters Pee Wee the elephant; and how, broke and alone, she hits the road on a succession of dangerous yet spiritually uplifting adventures. This volume also includes an index, and a biographical essay by Jeet Heer.

The complete daily comics from 1924 to 1927.
name: Volume One: Will Tomorrow Ever Come?
Captured by Giant Warriors and Imprisioned in the Ogre's Tower!

description:
Avalon Denied

King Arthur has not been killed in the last epic battle against his bastard son Modred, but instead continues to rule. However, the division amongst his men continues and he struggles to maintain control. Modred has also survived, now imprisoned in Merlin's dungeon, and more treachery is revealed as he will do anything to exact revenge against his father and the Kingdom of Camelot.
name: Avalon Denied

description:
While Cyclops, Emma and Wolverine are off in Japan dealing with giant monsters, something dire happens that demands the X-Men's attention. With their leaders away, should the X-Men deny their help? HELL NO! Storm, Colossus and Kitty Pryde join Beast and Agent Brand to take on the Brood. But when intergalactic law prevents the destruction of an enemy who can only be defeated by extermination, the X-Men have a problem. Are Storm and her crew up to the task? And what is Cyclops going to say when he learns of this? Plus: join us for a special told-in-one story with emma Frost and Danger delivering on a promise back in ASTONISHING X-MEN #24. Don't miss this confrontation that has been brewing since 2008!

Collecting ASTONISHING X-MEN #38, #40, #42 and #43 - plus UNCANNY X-MEN #162 (1982), featuring the classic battle between Wolverine and the Brood!
name: HC

volume.name: Astonishing X-Men: Children of the Brood

description: The Avenging Archer takes the stage in a collection of enough sensational solo adventures to fill anyone's quiver! First, watch out as Hawkeye encounters a genetically engineered monstrosity created by the insidious Secret Empire. But will this feral fiend prove to be friend or foe? Then, roll with the punches as Hawkeye gets battered by Batroc, assaulted by Oddball and trounced by the Taskmaster - all in a single thrilling one-shot. Finally, duck for cover when Hawkeye participates in a rocky three-part reunion! Ready, aim, fire - this Marvelous masterpiece hits the mark! Collecting HAWKEYE (1994) #1-4, HAWKEYE: EARTH'S MIGHTIEST MARKSMAN and material from MARVEL COMICS PRESENTS (1988) #159-161.
name: HC

description: When Daken came to Los Angeles, he believed the position of West Coast Kingpin was there for the taking. But the City of Angels has a new crime lord, the 'Claws' serial killer continues to cause carnage in the dark areas of the Hollywood Hills, and the Heat drug's grip on Daken is growing daily - scarring his mind and body. It's the perfect time, then, for Daken to find himself battling the Avenger with multiple personalities: Moon Knight! And when the shadow king of the Hollywood Hills is revealed, Daken suddenly finds himself the most wanted man in America - with the entire LAPD and the FBI on his tail! Can Daken save Donna Kiel when he's at his weakest? Does he even want to? Collecting DAKEN: DARK WOLVERINE #13-19.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Daken: Dark Wolverine: The Pride Comes Before The Fall

description: The "Terrible Seven", the Sumerian demons unleashed by the followers of Namtar, are raging in the halls of the Museum of Richmond, spreading horror and blood. While Zagor is facing Udug, the Black Lion, someone tries to steal the crown of Dumuzi ... Who? Perhaps the evil Fazahar, the magician who awakened the mummies from their sleep. Or is there someone else who is plotting to take over the crown of the ancient ruler? And, above all, why is that jewel so important?
name: Tranelli e veleni

description: The members of X-Factor - Cyclops, Jean Grey, Iceman, Beast and Archangel - are professionals through and through. But when the likes of Sabretooth, a cadre of vampires and a threat from an alternate dystopian future wage war against our heroes, it's no big surprise things get a little out of control even for them! Collecting X-FACTOR (1986) #51-59 and ANNUAL #4-5; X-FACTOR: PRISONER OF LOVE; MARVEL FANFARE (1982) #50; and material from FANTASTIC FOUR ANNUAL #23, NEW MUTANTS ANNUAL #6 and X-MEN ANNUAL #14.
name: Volume Four

description: Red Hulk's most dangerous dust-ups yet! As the hammer-wielders continue their campaign of fear and terror, Red Hulk takes up arms against the newly deified Ben Grimm, the FF's Thing! It's bruiser vs. bruiser as two of the world's strongest battle it out in an all-out brawl that will shake the world! And no one is watching closer than M.O.D.O.K.! Plus: Omegex, a deadly force from beyond the far reaches of space, has awakened - and he wants Red Hulk! Our Crimson Crusader has fought battles of massive scale, faced villains of great strength and guile, and even punched a Watcher! But what can he do against a destroyer of entire worlds? And with Red Hulk on the ropes, when it seems the situation can't get any worse, super villainess extraordinaire Zero/One and her henchman Black Fog arrive. Collecting HULK #37-41.
name: Fear Itself: Hulk

description: Blending elements of crime noir with classic monster horror, FERALS #1 begins with the personal tale of Officer Dale Chesnutt, a lawman in the sleepy town of Cypress. Folks are turning up not just dead, but slaughtered in bestial fashion. His investigation leads him to a tantalizing woman and a mystery that dates back centuries. It starts with small town people, folks with their own little dynamic, and a small town cop who is a charmer, a womanizer, a screw-up, says Lapham. He suddenly is hit by the stray bullets and finds himself in a whole new world thats plenty dark and twisted.

Available for purchase at the finest comic shops and specialty stores, FERALS #2 continues the bloody, brutal tale of Officer Dale Chesnutt, a small town lawman drawn into an ancient culture of primal instinct and secrets worth killing over. Residents of Cypress, including his friends, are being hunted and torn apart by a fearsome beast. Reeling from the loss, Chesnutt is seduced by a mysterious woman, and becomes the target for the murderous, cunning werewolf that is terrorizing his town. Now, after suffering a terrible personal loss, Chesnutt finds himself a suspect on the wrong side of the law, and on a collision course with an animal that can eviscerate its prey with tooth and claw. How will our so-called hero survive?

Cover: Leigh Gallagher (Judge Dredd)

  • Judge Dredd - Day of Chaos - Eve of Destruction (part 6) (John Wagner - Ben Willsher)
  • Grey Area - The Do (Dan Abnett - Lee Carter)
  • Nikolai Dante - The Wedding of Jena Makarov (part 8) (Robbie Morrison - Simon Fraser)
  • Absalom - Ghosts of London (part 6) (Gordon Rennie - Tiernen Trevallion)
  • Strontium Dog - The Life and Death of Johnny Alpha - Chapter Two: The Project (part 8) (John Wagner - Carlos and Hector Ezquerra)
name: Prog 1770

description: The treasure of Jean Lafitte is tempting to many: Digging to Bill, who is allied with the pirate John Connor and has done away with him a former accomplice of Lafitte, the pirate Barbe-en-Feu and its acolytes, the mysterious Denise, who was enamored of the young Jacques Lassalle. Meanwhile, behind the scenes, the same Lafitte prepares his return to the scene!
name: Il Tesoro di Jean Lafitte

description: Barbe-en-Feu kidnaps Digging Bill and Jacques with the intent to find out if they know where to find the treasure of Jean Lafitte. To free them, Zagor has to penetrate in the inaccessible lair of the pirate, in the heart of reed marshes where danger lurks at every step.
name: I pirati del golfo

description: The Pride, Lafitte's ship, is en route to Africa. The goal is the dark Skeleton Island. It is here that there will be the final battle for the possession of the treasure of Barbe-en-Feu and Lafitte. But another threat is looming over Zagor and his friends: Jacques, in his dreams, begins to be haunted by Marie Laveau, the beautiful voodoo witch!
name: Destinazione Africa!

description: Who would you want to solve your mystery: Scooby-Doo's nose or high-tech ghost-hunting equipment? When both are put to the test to find out what's been haunting the old silk mill, you can only imagine who wins (even though he might not want this prize).
name: Mile High Horror!

description: The armies of FEAR ITSELF are mounting on every side, and even the gods have turned their backs on Earth. With humanity facing its gravest threat yet, Steve Rogers and his Secret Avengers will be forced to make some hard choices about what's just in times of war. With the world falling apart and the Avengers in disarray, the SECRET AVENGERS spotlight shines on Beast, Valkyrie and Black Widow. Plus: The secret is out! Word of Steve Rogers' clandestine operations has leaked, kicking off a global race by the Secret Avengers to save compromised superhuman assets before they can be taken off the board! Collecting SECRET AVENGERS #12.1 and #13-15, and FEAR ITSELF: BLACK WIDOW #1.
name: HC/TPB

description: There may not be another 'next chapter' in the life of the Amazing Spider-Man if the villains in this volume get their way! Featuring such classic antagonists as Kraven the Hunter, Dr. Octopus, the Vulture and the Blob - not to mention alternate versions of Green Goblin, Electro and the Red Skull - this riotous roster reads like a veritable who's who of Spider-rogues! Plus: the return of Venom! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1999) #7-12, and PETER PARKER: SPIDER-MAN (1999) #7-12 and ANNUAL '99.
name: Volume Two
